-- Vietnam Stock Movers: Rang Dong Light, Construction 47, Habubank
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-05-09T08:06:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/vietnam-equity-movers-rang-dong-light-source-construction-47.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Vietnam trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in  Ho Chi Minh City .
The  VN Index (VNINDEX) , the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, fell 0.1 percent to 487.62.  Rang Dong Light Source & Vacuum Flask Joint-Stock Co. (RAL
VN), a maker of thermos flasks and fluorescent lighting
products, advanced 4.7 percent to 36,000 dong. First-quarter net
income increased 19 percent to 32 billion dong ($1.5 million),
the company said in a statement on the bourse’s website. Revenue
rose 22 percent to 614 billion dong in the same period, it said.  Construction Join-Stock Co. 47 (C47)  (C47 VN) climbed 4.7 percent
to 13,500 dong, the highest close since April 15, 2011. The
company will pay a dividend of 1,250 dong a share on June 4, it
said in a statement filed on the exchange’s website.  Hanoi Building Commercial Joint-Stock Bank (HBB)  , also
known as Habubank, dropped 1.5 percent to 6,600 dong.
Shareholders of Saigon-Hanoi Bank agreed to a merger with
Habubank in a May 5 meeting, according to a statement on Saigon-
Hanoi bank’s website.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
